1. Azure Boards kya hai?

- Azure DevOps ka project management aur work tracking tool hai.
- Agile teams apna kaam track karne ke liye use karti hain.
- Jira, Trello, Asana jaise tools ka alternative hai, lekin Azure DevOps ke andar built-in hai.
- Ismein Kanban boards, backlogs, sprints, dashboards — sab kuch hota hai.

2. Kyun use karte hain?

- Team ka kaam visualize hota hai — kya chal raha hai, kispe hai, kitna bacha hai
- Sprint planning aur capacity tracking
- Bugs, features, tasks — sab ek jagah
- Git commits, pull requests se directly link hota hai (traceability)


3. Azure Board Processes: Basic, Agile, Scrum, CMMI

- Jab Azure Boards mein project banate ho, toh pehle Process Template select karna padta hai. 

***  Yeh 4 options hain:

1. Basic (Sabse simple)         = Beginners ke liye best.
Sirf 3 work item types: Epic → Issue → Task

No complex ceremonies, direct kaam shuru kar sakte ho.

2. Agile (Microsoft ka Agile template)
Work items: Epic → Feature → User Story → Task

Iterations (Sprints) hote hain, lekin formal Scrum ceremonies nahi enforce karta.

Flexible hai - Agile principles follow karta hai without strict Scrum rules.

3. Scrum (Sabse zyada use hota hai industry mein)
Work items: Epic → Feature → Product Backlog Item (PBI) → Task → Bug

Formal Scrum follow karta hai: Sprints, Product Backlog, Sprint Backlog, Burndown charts.

PBI = User Story ka equivalent (Microsoft ne iska naam PBI rakha hai)

4. CMMI (Capability Maturity Model Integration)
Enterprise/government projects ke liye. Heavy documentation aur formal processes required hote hain.

Requirement → Change Request → Task → Bug → Issue

Change tracking, formal approvals - sab strict hota hai.
- Basic se shuru karo, phir Scrum pe aao — yeh real-world mein sabse zyada use hota hai.
- Work Items Explained: Epics, Issues, and Tasks
- Work Item = Azure Boards mein ek unit of work.

Hierarchy samajh lo:

- Epic (Sabse bada)
- Bada business initiative — months tak chal sakta hai.
- Example: "Launch New Mobile App" ya "Migrate to Cloud"


Feature
Epic ka ek meaningful part — user ke liye koi functionality.
Example: "User Login System" ya "Payment Gateway Integration"
User Story / PBI / Issue


Feature ka ek chota tukda — end user ki ek specific need.
Example: "As a user, I want to login with Google so that I don't need to remember password"
Agile mein User Story, Scrum mein PBI, Basic mein Issue kehte hain.


Task
Sabse chota unit — ek User Story/PBI complete karne ke liye jo technical steps chahiye.
Example: "Create database schema for users", "Write API endpoint for OAuth", "Write unit tests"
ek diagram/cheatsheet dikhata hai — kaise Epic se lekar Task tak hierarchy banti hai.
